19. Order flow
Customer scans table QR
Frontend opens tenant page
Frontend loads menu via /api/v1/*
Backend detects tenant
Backend reads tenant DB
Customer adds items
Frontend sends order to /api/v1/orders
Backend creates order
Backend saves order menus/options/totals
Payment starts or order remains pending
Invoice/payment/fiskaly logic runs depending on flow





20. Admin order flow
Admin/staff creates order in admin panel
Order saved in backend tables
Items saved in ti_order_menus
Options saved in ti_order_menu_options
Status may be saved in ti_status_history
Payment QR may be generated
Customer can scan QR to pay
Payment provider handles payment
Order should become paid
Invoice should show Fiskaly QR if Fiskaly transaction exists





21. QR payment feature
Admin can create order
Customer can scan QR to pay existing order
Frontend should load pending QR order
Backend should process pay-existing flow
Payment provider should confirm payment
Order/payment status should update
Invoice should show correct payment and Fiskaly data






